HEADWORD: parasiticidal
<hw>par`a*sit`i*cid"al</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Capable of destroying
parasites, especially capable of expelling or destroying parasitic
worms.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> anthelmintic, anthelminthic, helminthic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

